  "prompt": "Why do girls wear sports bras?",
  "response": "Girls wear sports bras for several reasons:\n\n1. **Support**: Sports bras provide support to the breasts during physical activities, reducing movement and discomfort. This is particularly important during high-impact activities like running or jumping.\n\n2. **Comfort**: They are designed to be more comfortable than regular bras, often made from moisture-wicking fabrics that help keep the skin dry during exercise.\n\n3. **Minimizing Discomfort**: Physical activity can cause breast discomfort and pain if not properly supported. Sports bras help minimize this discomfort.\n\n4. **Breathability**: Most sports bras are designed with breathability in mind, allowing for better airflow during workouts, which can help regulate temperature and enhance comfort.\n\n5. **Encouraging Participation**: Wearing a properly fitted sports bra can make exercise and sports more enjoyable, encouraging girls to participate in physical activities confidently.\n\n6. **Prevention of Injury**: Some studies suggest that adequate support can help prevent sagging and potential damage to breast tissue over time.\n\nOverall, sports bras play a significant role in ensuring that girls can engage in physical activity safely and comfortably.",
